x4codes.hlp: INFN Laboratori Nazionali di Frascati, Frascati, Italy

x4freetext: FRASCATI NATIONAL LABORATORIES LADON.
THE  TARGET  MATERIALS  CONSISTED   OF  METAL FILMS OF
HIGH-PURITY NATURAL GOLD,  ABOUT 1.4 MG/CM**2,  LEAD,
ABOUT 4.1 MG/CM**2,  AND BISMITH, ABOUT 5.7 MG/CM**2,
PREPARED BY VACUUM EVAPORATION ON ABOUT 3.5 CM X  3.5
CM  THIN  FOILS  1.72  MG/CM**2  THICK  OF  MYLAR  AS
SUPPORTS,  AND THE FILNS OF NATURAL THORIUM,  NATURAL
URANIUM  AND 93 %  -ENRICHED U-235 OXIDES PRODUCED BY
THE "PARLODION IGNITION" METHOD ON ABOUT 4 CM X 4  CM
SHEETS  OF  MUSCOVITE  MICA  ABOUT 25 MG/CM**2 THICK,
WHICH SERVED AS SUPPORTS AND/OR DETECTORS FOR FISSION
FRAGMENTS.
100 MICRON THICK MACROFOL N, BAYER AG, FOILS AND
MICA FOILS.
THE DIRECT FISSION FRAGMENT TRACK COUNTING.
TO  OBTAIN THE FINAL VALUES OF THE PHYSICAL QUANTITIES
AND ASSOCIATED  ERRORS,  THE  DATA  HAVE BEEN TREATED
TAKING INTO  ACCOUNT  THE  GEOMETRY  OF  IRRADIATION,
STATISTICS   OF   TRACK   COUNTING   AND  EFFICIENCY,
REGISTRATION EFFICIENCY, ENERGY ABSORPTION EFFECTS OF
FISSION FRAGMENTS BY THICK-TARGET SAMPLES AU, PB, AND
BI, AND BACKGROUND.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: STATISTICAL   ERRORS   ARE   GIVEN.   THE
SYSTEMATIC UNCERTAINTY WAS ESTIMATED TO BE EQUAL TO 6
%  FOR TH AND U TARGETS,  23 % FOR PB AND BI TARGETS,
AND 30 %  FOR AU TARGETS WHILE THE  STATISTICAL  ONCE
AMOUNTED TO 15 %  FOR U-235,  5 %  FOR U-238, 0 % FOR
TH-232,  22 %  FOR BI-209, 41 % FOR PB-NAT., AND 50 %
FOR AU-197 NUCLEI.
DATA  WERE  PREPARED  IN THE MSU INP CDFE  BY
V.V.VARLAMOV.
ABSOLUTE   CROSS   SECTION   MEASUREMENTS   FOR    THE
PHOTOFISSION REACTIONS  OF AU-197,  PB-NAT.,  BI-209,
TH-232, U-238,  AND U-235 MUCLEI HAVE BEEN  PERFORMED
AT AN   INCIDENT   PHOTON  ENERGY  OF  69  MEV  USING
MONOCHROMATIC AND FULLY POLARIZED  PHOTON  BEAMS  AND
DIELECTRIC FISSION-TRACK DETECTORS. NUCLEAR FISSILITY
VALUES HAVE  BEEN  OBTAINED  AND   RESULTS   ARE   IN
AGREEMENT WITH   THOSE   FROM   OTHER   LABORATORIES,
ALTHOUGH IN SOME  CASES  DISCREPANCIES  ARE  OBSERVED
BETWEEN ONE  OTHER.  FOR  NUCLEI  IN  THE  REGION  OF
ACTINIDES THE FISSILITY RESULT IS >  0.4,  WHILE  FOR
AU, PB,  AND  BI  NUCLEI  IT  ONLY  IS ABOUT 10**-3 -
10**-2. RESULTS HAVE BEEN INTERPRETED IN TERMS OF THE
PRIMARY LEVINGER`S        QUASIDEUTERON       NUCLEAR
PHOTOABSORPTION FOLLOWED   BY    A    MECHANISM    OF
EVAPORATION-FISSION COMPETITION   FOR   THE   EXCITED
NUCLEI. SHELL EFFECTS HAVE BEEN TAKEN  INTO  ACCOUNT,
AND THEY  ARE  CLEARLY  MANIFESTED  WHEN FISSILITY IS
EVALUATED. THE INFLUENCE OF  PHOTON  POLARIZATION  ON
PHOTOFISSION OF U-238 ALSO HAS BEEN INVESTIGATED, AND
RESULTS HAVE SHOWN ISOTROPY IN THE FRAGMENT  AZIMUTAL
DISTRIBUTION.
